I will call this place a dive bar in Staten Island. However, it is a classy dive bar. I don't normally frequent this neighborhood but the clientele at this bar seem to be extremely local ranging from the old school Italian/ Irish population and of course catering to the millennials. As I sat at the bar and listened to the Italian drawal and the f-bomb dropping naturally and often, with conversations regarding the Yankees, Mets, Rangers,  Giants and the Jets I couldn't help but feel at home. Being a native NY'er and living in Philadelphia will do that to you. It was very nice eating/drinking here and the food is great. I can only speak to the wings which apparently are the best wings in America according to food and wine. I had the Buffalo city style wings that are supposed to be the originals and they lived up to the billing. They have plenty of beers on tap. They have plenty of places to sit. The bar is not huge but it serves its purpose. All in all the people were very pleasant. And looking at all the pictures of the food which I did not try it all looks awesome. In fact the street where it's located there are lots of nice eateries so if you're in the neighborhood you should try them all. When I come back to Staten Island I certainly will return here.
